And they also visited the Briar Dene pub on The Links, Whitley Bay, and threatened David Horgan - boss of the Sir John Fitzgerald pub chain - that they would park 200 caravans on the pub car park.

Adams, 46, and Cunningham Snr, 48, both of Askern, South Yorkshire, were handed eight-and-a-half year sentences and made the subject of a director disqualification order for five years.

