Terence Cunningham Jnr, 26, of Askern, was handed a six-year jail term and a director disqualification order.

Darren Squire, also of Askern, will serve four years in prison. All were sentenced for a charge of conspiracy to blackmail.

Michael Howley, 72, of Messingham, Scunthorpe, who is already behind bars, was found guilty of money laundering. He was given four years.

